knowledge: Existential crisis . An existential crisis is a moment at which an individual questions if their life has meaning, purpose, or value. It may be commonly, but not necessarily, tied to depression or inevitably negative speculations on purpose in life. (e.g., "if one day I will be forgotten, what is the point of all of my work?") This issue of the meaning and purpose of human existence is a major focus of the philosophical tradition of existentialism.
